    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but even \"resting\" feels like another performance. i'm just staying in this body because it's what people expect. if the person who mattered is truly dead, then what's the point in maintaining the remains? it feels more like a burden than a life. it's like i'm just waiting for the rest of me to catch up to what happened years ago.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
